The paper discusses a methodology for examining the accuracy of uncertain inference systems (UIS), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with probabilistic models and updating formulae, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.IT. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and comparisons, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS.
